mim.author: ESHUMER
mim.name: ECIM_SubEquipTraceM
mim.description: This fragment is used to manage the trace sessions on the managed element. Once the trace is activated the trace data can be collected. The trace data can be sent via streaming or file transfer depending on the trace capabilities specified.

struct.name: TraceTarget
struct.description: Trace target includes the target type and the identity.

structMember.name: targetType
structMember.description: This defines the Trace target type.

structMember.name: targetIdentity
structMember.description: This is the Trace target identity for first UE (Originating UE). This field is mandatory.

structMember.name: terminatingTargetIdentity
structMember.description: This is the Trace target identity for the second UE (Terminating UE). This field is optional and valid when attribute betweenUsersEnabled = true, in TraceCapabilities MOC.

structMember.name: traceReference
structMember.description: The TraceReference is a unique ID. It identifies the trace session that has been created by the activation of the trace Job on the Managed Element. The Trace Reference parameter shall be globally unique and composed as follows: MCC+MNC+Trace ID, where the MCC and MNC are coming with the trace activation request from the EM/NM to identify one PLMN containing the EM/NM, and Trace ID is a 3 byte Octet String.

struct.name: TraceParameter
struct.description: It defines the parameter name and its corresponding value.

structMember.name: parameterName
structMember.description: Parameter name is the attribute, based on which filter is applied.

structMember.name: parameterValue
structMember.description: This is actual value of the parameter selected by the parameterName.

enum.name: ActivationType
enum.description: There are two activation types, management-based activation and signaling-based activation.

enumMember.name: MANAGEMENT
enumMember.description: In Management, the activation is done directly on the Network Elements. Management activation/deactivation is where a trace session is activated/deactivated in different Network Elements directly using the management interfaces of those Network Elements.

enumMember.name: SIGNALING
enumMember.description: In Signaling, the activation can be done via another Network Element. Signaling activation/deactivation is where a trace session is activated/deactivated in different Network Elements using the signaling interfaces between those elements, so that the Network Elements may forward the activation/deactivation.

enum.name: JobType
enum.description: This defines the possible job types.

enum.name: FilterMethod
enum.description: Filter method defines whether single or multiple values can be selected for a filter attribute.

enumMember.name: SINGLE_SELECT
enumMember.description: Only one value can be given to the attribute.

enumMember.name: MULTI_SELECT
enumMember.description: More than one value can be assigned to the attribute.

enum.name: TimePeriod
enum.description: Defines the periodic duration of the log file recording.

class.name: SubEquipTraceM
class.description: This fragment is used to manage the trace sessions on the managed element. When the trace is activated, the trace data can be collected. The trace data can be sent via streaming or file transfer depending on the specified trace capabilities.

attribute.name: subEquipTraceMId
attribute.description: Holds the name used when identifying the MO.

class.name: TraceJob
class.description: The trace job defines all the trace information. This information is used to activate and configure a trace session on the Managed Element.

attribute.name: traceJobId
attribute.description: Holds the name used when identifying the MO.

attribute.name: description
attribute.description: Describes the content and purpose of the job.

attribute.name: activationType
attribute.description: Specifies the trace-activation type to be used. There are two types of activation: Management activation and deactivation is a trace session that is activated or deactivated in different NEs directly by using the management interfaces of those NEs. Signaling activation and deactivation is a trace session that is activated or deactivated in different NEs that use the signaling interfaces between those elements to enable the NEs to forward the activation or deactivation.

attribute.name: jobType
attribute.description: The Job type parameter defines the trace job type. The Job type parameter is an enumerated type with the following values: - Trace only (0)

attribute.name: traceTarget
attribute.description: Specifies the target object of the Trace. It is used to define one or multiple UEs depending on the trace requirement.

attribute.name: requestedJobState
attribute.description: This is the requested state of the trace job. It represents the state that the job has been ordered to reach. Possible values: ACTIVE, STOPPED

attribute.name: currentJobState
attribute.description: This is the current state of the trace job. Possible values: ACTIVATING, ACTIVE, DEACTIVATING, STOPPED, FAILED

attribute.name: reportingPeriod
attribute.description: Specifies how often trace data is made available. The value must be valid according to the supportedReportingPeriods set by the Managed Element.

attribute.name: streamingURI
attribute.description: Specifies the location (URI) where the trace data is to be streamed. Only valid if streamOutputEnabled is set to true.

attribute.name: streamOutputEnabled
attribute.description: StreamOutputEnabled when set to "true" means that only Streaming will be done. And if set to "false", means only file Pull will be done. For a single trace job either file Pull or Streaming can be selected.

attribute.name: fileCompressionType
attribute.description: Compression Type to be applied to file output. Only valid when streamOutputEnabled = false. If this attribute is not set, no compression will be applied to the file output. Can only be assigned a value according to the capability supportedCompressionTypes in the FilePullCapabilities MOC.

attribute.name: streamCompressionType
attribute.description: Compression Type to be applied to stream output. Only valid when streamOutputEnabled = true. If this attribute is not set, no compression will be applied to the stream output. Can only be assigned a value according to the capability supportedCompressionTypes in the StreamingCapabilities MOC.

class.name: StreamingCapabilities
class.description: Trace capabilities related to data streaming.

attribute.name: streamingCapabilitiesId
attribute.description: Holds the name used when identifying the MO.

attribute.name: supportedCompressionTypes
attribute.description: Defines the compression type for data streaming.

class.name: TraceProfile
class.description: Defines the trace information to be used to activate and configure a trace profile. This profile must only be used if the job type is configured for Trace on the Managed Element.

attribute.name: traceProfileId
attribute.description: Holds the name used when identifying the MO.

attribute.name: traceParameter
attribute.description: This defines the attributes and their values depending on which filter would be applied.

class.name: FilePullCapabilities
class.description: Defines the file capabilities when file transfer is PULL.

attribute.name: filePullCapabilitiesId
attribute.description: Holds the name used when identifying the MO.

attribute.name: outputDirectory
attribute.description: This is the location where trace data will be placed for file Pull. This is the directory location on the Managed Element.

attribute.name: allignedReportingPeriod
attribute.description: The Managed Element will align its reporting periods to the hour if set to TRUE.

attribute.name: supportedCompressionTypes
attribute.description: File compression type. This property is only valid for FILE transfer type.

attribute.name: supportedReportingPeriods
attribute.description: Specifies the list of reporting periods supported by the Managed Element.

class.name: TraceCapabilities
class.description: Defines the Trace Job related capabilities.

attribute.name: traceCapabilitiesId
attribute.description: Holds the name used when identifying the MO.

attribute.name: maxNoOfJobs
attribute.description: Defines the maximum number of trace jobs that can run in parallel on the Managed Element.

attribute.name: betweenUsersEnabled
attribute.description: Defines whether Managed Element supports the trace between two UEs. When set to true, it means that the trace job can be between two UEs, orignating and terminating.

attribute.name: maxNoOfUEs
attribute.description: Defines the permitted maximum number of UEs that can be traced.

class.name: TraceParameterType
class.description: This defines the Trace parameters, which are possible for the particular Network Element. All the attributes and their possible values and restrictions. TraceParamaterType MOs are created at design time as Instance models and installed on a system at initial configuration or Upgrade.

attribute.name: traceParameterTypeId
attribute.description: Holds the name used when identifying the MO.

attribute.name: isMandatory
attribute.description: This defines if the attribute value is mandatory to be entered or not.

attribute.name: selectionMethod
attribute.description: This defines whether single or multiple values can be entered for the seleceted attribute.

attribute.name: validValues
attribute.description: It contains the possible valid values, which can be entered.

attribute.name: defaultValue
attribute.description: This is the value which is selected if no value is given for an attribute.

attribute.name: description
attribute.description: Describes a brief detail for the selected parameter.

class.name: TraceParameterGroup
class.description: Describes the name, version and description of the group. This helps in identifying the interfaces, messages and other parameters valid for this group.

attribute.name: traceParameterGroupId
attribute.description: Holds the name used when identifying the MO.

attribute.name: groupVersion
attribute.description: Defines the version of this particular group.

attribute.name: description
attribute.description: Contains the details relating to this group.

class.name: ManagedObject
class.description: The ManagedObject MO represents a generic MO type. It does not represent any real resource in the system and can therefore not be instanciated. It is used as a MO-reference that can refer to multiple MO types.
